# Risk Management & Position Sizing

## What This Skill Covers
All logic related to how much to risk per trade, protecting the overall bankroll, enforcing daily/weekly loss limits, and scaling size up or down based on strategy confidence and recent performance.

## Core Sizing Model: Fixed Fractional
```python
# Risk a fixed % of current bankroll per trade
position_size = current_bankroll * RISK_PER_TRADE_PCT

# Example: $1000 bankroll, 2% risk = $20 max loss per trade
# With 2% stop loss: position = $20 / 0.02 = $1000 notional
# But Kalshi contracts are binary — size = contracts to buy
```

## Parameters (Tunable)
```python
RISK_PER_TRADE_PCT       = 0.02    # 2% of bankroll per trade baseline
MAX_RISK_PER_TRADE_PCT   = 0.03    # Hard ceiling — never exceed 3%
MIN_RISK_PER_TRADE_PCT   = 0.005   # Minimum during drawdown protection

DAILY_LOSS_LIMIT_PCT     = 0.06    # Stop trading today if down 6% on the day
WEEKLY_LOSS_LIMIT_PCT    = 0.15    # Stop trading this week if down 15%
MAX_DRAWDOWN_PCT         = 0.20    # Pause entire bot if down 20% from peak

MAX_CONCURRENT_POSITIONS = 1       # One position at a time per market
MAX_TOTAL_EXPOSURE_PCT   = 0.10    # Never have more than 10% of bankroll at risk simultaneously

# Confidence multipliers (applied to base risk)
HIGH_CONVICTION_MULT     = 1.3     # OBI + ROC both agree
SINGLE_SIGNAL_MULT       = 0.7     # Only one strategy firing
DRAWDOWN_REDUCTION_MULT  = 0.5     # Reduce size when in drawdown
```

## Position Sizing Logic
```python
class PositionSizer:
    def __init__(self, initial_bankroll):
        self.bankroll = initial_bankroll
        self.peak_bankroll = initial_bankroll
        self.daily_start_bankroll = initial_bankroll
        self.weekly_start_bankroll = initial_bankroll
        self.trades_today = []
        self.trades_this_week = []

    def calculate_size(self, signal_confidence, strategy_name):
        """
        signal_confidence: "HIGH" (both signals agree) | "NORMAL" | "LOW"
        Returns: dollar amount to risk on this trade
        """
        if not self.can_trade():
            return 0

        base_risk = self.bankroll * RISK_PER_TRADE_PCT

        # Apply confidence multiplier
        multipliers = {
            "HIGH":   HIGH_CONVICTION_MULT,
            "NORMAL": 1.0,
            "LOW":    SINGLE_SIGNAL_MULT,
        }
        adjusted_risk = base_risk * multipliers.get(signal_confidence, 1.0)

        # Apply drawdown reduction
        drawdown = self._current_drawdown()
        if drawdown > 0.10:
            adjusted_risk *= DRAWDOWN_REDUCTION_MULT

        # Clamp to hard limits
        max_risk = self.bankroll * MAX_RISK_PER_TRADE_PCT
        min_risk = self.bankroll * MIN_RISK_PER_TRADE_PCT
        final_risk = max(min_risk, min(max_risk, adjusted_risk))

        return round(final_risk, 2)

    def can_trade(self):
        """Check all circuit breakers before allowing any trade."""
        if self._daily_loss() >= DAILY_LOSS_LIMIT_PCT:
            return False, "DAILY_LOSS_LIMIT"
        if self._weekly_loss() >= WEEKLY_LOSS_LIMIT_PCT:
            return False, "WEEKLY_LOSS_LIMIT"
        if self._current_drawdown() >= MAX_DRAWDOWN_PCT:
            return False, "MAX_DRAWDOWN_HALT"
        if self._current_exposure() >= MAX_TOTAL_EXPOSURE_PCT:
            return False, "MAX_EXPOSURE"
        return True, None

    def _current_drawdown(self):
        self.peak_bankroll = max(self.peak_bankroll, self.bankroll)
        return (self.peak_bankroll - self.bankroll) / self.peak_bankroll

    def _daily_loss(self):
        return (self.daily_start_bankroll - self.bankroll) / self.daily_start_bankroll

    def _weekly_loss(self):
        return (self.weekly_start_bankroll - self.bankroll) / self.weekly_start_bankroll

    def _current_exposure(self):
        # Sum of all open position risk amounts / bankroll
        return sum(p["risk_amount"] for p in open_positions()) / self.bankroll

    def record_trade(self, pnl):
        """Call after every trade closes."""
        self.bankroll += pnl
        self.trades_today.append(pnl)
        self.trades_this_week.append(pnl)

    def reset_daily(self):
        """Call at start of each trading day."""
        self.daily_start_bankroll = self.bankroll
        self.trades_today = []

    def reset_weekly(self):
        """Call at start of each trading week."""
        self.weekly_start_bankroll = self.bankroll
        self.trades_this_week = []
```

## Circuit Breakers — Never Override These
```
Daily Loss > 6%      → Stop all trading, resume tomorrow
Weekly Loss > 15%    → Stop all trading, resume next Monday
Drawdown > 20%       → Full bot pause, manual review required
Exposure > 10%       → No new positions until existing ones close
```

## Bankroll Update Flow
```python
# On every trade close:
1. Calculate actual PnL (after Kalshi fees)
2. Call position_sizer.record_trade(pnl)
3. Log new bankroll to persistent state
4. Check circuit breakers — halt if triggered
5. Persist state to disk (never rely on in-memory only)
```

